The website was great! It was really informative and very pretty so it was nice to navigate. I did notice some typos here and there (some words were repeated) and while I know that BMI is widely used medically, it's not necessarily the best thing for people to use to track their weight. I also appreciated the diversity of the photos used on the site and the diversity of the women featured in the "Women's Stories" section but I was really disappointed in the lack of diversity in the research team. I am also a researcher (based out of UT Austin) focusing on reproductive health and am a BIPOC. I find that BIPOC voices are sorely missing when talking about health so I do wish there was more diversity in the lead researchers. As noted throughout the site, menopause and peri-menopause aren't talked about enough and can come seemingly out of nowhere for many women (it did for me!). I think this can be compounded in cultures where there is increased stigma about anything related to reproductive health.
